Key issues include but are not limited to multi-modal transportation opportunities, environmental justice, traffic congestion, air quality, hazardous materials, ROW, noise, wildlife, cumulative impacts with other projects, context-sensitive design, impacts to Jefferson County airport, and public/community involvement.
This contract is a task order contract and no task order for work beyond an approved DEIS and associated public hearing will be issued until: Â· Â· Â· A funding plan is developed and approved by FHWA; The alternatives are included in the DRCOG Regional Transportation Plan (RTP), and; FHWA approves the DEIS and the project enters into Preliminary Engineering/Final Environmental Impact Statement (FEIS) in compliance with applicable regulations and requirements.
