A1.5 PROJECT GOAL This project is intended to recommend improvements related to the following issues: Â· Â· Â· Â· Â· Â· Â· System Connectivity Multi-modal forms of transportation Transportation Demand and Capacity Improved Safety Modal Interrelationships Improved Levels-of-Service Address deteriorating structures and roadways
A1.6 PROJECT MILESTONES CDOT and the local agencies in the area of the Northwest Corridor have agreed to foster an aggressive schedule to complete all necessary studies and documents as rapidly as possible within the constraints of NEPA and its associated regulations.
To that end, the Consultant will be expected to utilize environmental streamlining methods.
Based upon preliminary assessments of the features of the Project, CDOT and the local agencies have estimated the time period for the work described in this scope to be approximately 660 calendar days to FEIS, under an aggressive schedule.
Since this is a task order-based project, milestones for the overall development of the Northwest Corridor EIS, ROD and Basic Engineering will be established/negotiated between parties as the study project progresses.
Anticipated milestones for the overall development of the Northwest Corridor DEIS and Basic Engineering include, but are necessarily limited to, the following list: DEIS Project Milestones Notice to Proceed Prepare detailed Scope of Work, including Public Involvement Plan and Project Management Plan Partnering Session Start Data Collection of Baseline Conditions Start Development of Full Range of Alternatives Conduct Agency and Public Scoping Meetings Start Alternatives Analysis Complete geotechnical and preliminary ROW investigation Complete Phase I and II Hazardous Materials Report Complete preliminary Traffic Report Engineering Survey of Corridor Complete Prepare various sections of draft DEIS, including Draft 4(f) Section if required.
