Field review of alternatives and associated environmental impacts.
Coordination of engineering, DEIS review and approval process.
Identification and analysis of previous studies completed in the Northwest Corridor.
Preparation, revision, and distribution of the DEIS document, including a first preliminary DEIS, a preliminary DEIS and then DEIS for signatures (each dated on the outside cover for easy identification).
Preparation of a Basic Engineering summary report.
This report documents the engineering studies completed in order to evaluate the environmental impacts, mitigation measures, and costs of the proposed project.
Preparation of a Master Schedule consistent with the MOU schedule, reflecting completion of the EIS, Basic Engineering, ROD, Final Engineering, Cash Flow, Construction and Implementation.
Preparation of a funding plan.
Assist in DRCOG conformity /RTP/TIP actions.
All submittals must be accepted by the PMT or designee.
