Schedule review and adjustment Other required progress meetings and/or plans include: Technical Committee Meetings A Technical Committee will be set for the PMT, and private sector agencies along the corridor, Programs (OEP), DRCOG, FHWA, FAA, DOE, meet to provide technical input in order to gain recommended to the Policy Committee.
Policy Committee Meetings A Policy Committee shall be established by the PMT, including CDOT, Northwest Corridor representatives, and FHWA representatives.
This committee will meet to provide policy level consensus in findings that will be carried forward as part of the EIS.
Executive Oversight Committee Meetings An Executive Oversight Committee (EOC) shall be established by the PMT.
The Committee will be composed of the Executive Director of CDOT and the FHWA Division Administrator.
Corridors Coordination Meetings Executive management through corridor managers, including consultants, will participate in Corridor Coordination meetings.
The Corridor Coordination meeting will be held once a month.
The purpose of these meetings is to manage issues that may impact multiple studies and review meeting dates and study milestone dates to reduce conflicts between studies.
The Consultant representative for the Northwest study will coordinate/alternate with consultant representatives on the other studies to prepare the agenda, conduct the meeting, and issue meeting minutes.
Other Agency Meetings Other agency meetings include anticipated meetings with federal, state and local agencies.
including representatives of local government along with CDOT's Office of Environmental USFWS, and CDPHE.
