A3.11 STRUCTURE REVIEW MEETING While the major structural design work is progressing, the Consultant shall meet periodically to review the work with the Structure Reviewer as defined in the CDOT Bridge Design Manual, Subsection 19.1.1C.
These meetings will be in addition to the Project Progress Meetings.
Minutes of these meetings shall be prepared by the consultant and submitted to the PMT, with a copy to the Structure Reviewers.
Typically, these Structure Review Meetings shall be no less than one every two months or more than one every two weeks.
The complexity of the structure shall be considered by the Structure Reviewers to determine their frequency.
The Consultant shall coordinate all the work tasks being accomplished by all parties to ensure project work completion on schedule.
A3.12 PARTNERING MEETING A Partnering Meeting will be held with CDOT, local governments, DRCOG, and FHWA personnel to confirm the project design elements, overall project development, and resolution of unresolved issues and determination of project specific QA/QC processes.
The consultant will facilitate in conducting this meeting and present the relevant design elements and criteria for agency confirmation.
