4.
Develop a data recovery plan to mitigate potential adverse effects to significant archaeological localities, as appropriate and necessary.
5.
Coordinate the mitigation plan with the PMT and/or their designated representative, State Historic Preservation Officer and other required agencies.
NOTE: the study area to be used for identifying resources is approximately one-half mile each side of any improvement.
To assess impacts, the study area is the extent of improvement.
